---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Israel Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/israel/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Cyprus for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/cyprus' },
  { title: 'Greece for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/greece' },
  { title: 'Italy for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/italy' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'israelFit', header: 'Israel Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '₪1,400-2,000/mo', israelFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '₪1,650-2,350/mo', israelFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '₪1,300-1,850/mo', israelFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '₪1,200-1,750/mo', israelFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Israeli HMOs', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'Mandatory', monthlyFrom: 'Health Tax', israelFit: 'For Citizens' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '₪1,300-2,000', annual: '₪15,600-24,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '₪1,800-2,700', annual: '₪21,600-32,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '₪2,400-3,600', annual: '₪28,800-43,200' },
  { category: 'Israeli HMO (Citizens)', monthly: 'Health Tax', annual: 'Comprehensive coverage' },
  { category: 'Private Supplementary', monthly: '₪200-600', annual: '₪2,400-7,200' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Israel 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Israel. World-class healthcare, Mediterranean climate, cultural richness, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Israel"
  subheadline="Israel offers world-renowned healthcare, Mediterranean lifestyle, rich history, and innovation culture—with strong options for Jewish seniors making aliyah."
  heroImage="/images/countries/israel-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Israel</h2>
  <p>
    Israel offers remarkable combination: world-class healthcare, Mediterranean climate, deep cultural and historical significance, and innovation-driven society. For Jewish seniors, making aliyah (immigration under Law of Return) provides automatic citizenship and healthcare access. Tel Aviv offers vibrant urban life while other areas provide more peaceful retirement.
  </p>

  <p>
    Tel Aviv delivers cosmopolitan beach lifestyle with excellent hospitals. Jerusalem offers spiritual significance and cooler climate. Haifa provides coastal living with good healthcare. Netanya and Herzliya attract retirees with beach access and good facilities.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; among world's best outcomes</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Hebrew; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> ₪8,000-15,000/month (~$2,200-4,100); high</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean; hot dry summers, mild winters</li>
      <li><strong>Aliyah:</strong> Law of Return provides citizenship pathway for Jews</li>
      <li><strong>Innovation:</strong> "Startup nation" with excellent medical tech</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Israel's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Israel has universal healthcare through four competing HMOs (kupot holim): Clalit, Maccabi, Leumit, and Meuhedet. All citizens must join one. Coverage is comprehensive and quality is excellent—Israel has among the world's best health outcomes. All HMOs provide core services; supplementary insurance adds extras.
  </p>

  <p>
    Israeli hospitals (Hadassah, Sheba, Ichilov, Rambam) are world-class with cutting-edge technology. Medical research is advanced. English is widely spoken in healthcare settings. The system is efficient despite high usage.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Aliyah and Healthcare</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Jewish individuals making aliyah receive immediate citizenship and healthcare access through the HMO system. The Jewish Agency assists with immigration. Upon arrival, you choose an HMO and receive comprehensive coverage funded through health tax. This is a significant benefit for eligible seniors.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Israel's immigration options depend heavily on Jewish status:
  </p>

  <h3>Law of Return (Aliyah)</h3>
  <p>
    Jews, children of Jews, grandchildren of Jews, and their spouses can immigrate under Law of Return. Immediate citizenship, full rights, HMO healthcare access. The primary pathway for eligible seniors.
  </p>

  <h3>A/5 Temporary Resident</h3>
  <p>
    For non-Jews with Israeli family connections or those married to Israelis. Provides residence but different healthcare pathway than aliyah.
  </p>

  <h3>B/1 Work Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Employment-based visa. Not typical for retirees but possible for those with skills Israel needs.
  </p>

  <h3>Tourism/Extended Stay</h3>
  <p>
    B/2 tourist visa allows 3 months. Extensions possible but not designed for permanent residence. Not a retirement pathway.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Israel depend on status:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Olim (Aliyah):</strong> Automatic HMO coverage through health tax</li>
    <li><strong>Non-citizens:</strong> International insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>Temporary residents:</strong> May need private coverage initially</li>
    <li><strong>Supplementary:</strong> Many Israelis add for extras</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Israel</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      For aliyah: HMO coverage is automatic and excellent. Consider supplementary for faster access and extras. For non-citizens: international insurance is essential—Israeli HMOs don't cover non-citizens. Ensure coverage at Israel's excellent hospitals if residing long-term without citizenship.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For non-citizen seniors or supplementary coverage, these providers work well:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Israel</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Israeli hospital network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Israeli HMOs:</strong> Excellent but for citizens/residents only</li>
    <li><strong>HMO Supplementary:</strong> Maccabi Sheli, Clalit Mushlam for extras</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from international providers for Israel.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs depend on citizenship status:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Make aliyah:</strong> If eligible, HMO coverage is comprehensive and affordable</li>
    <li><strong>HMO supplementary:</strong> ₪100-300/month adds faster access, second opinions</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Israeli care is excellent but not cheap</li>
    <li><strong>Travel exclusions:</strong> If staying in Israel, exclude other regions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Making Aliyah, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Jewish American retiring to Israel. $2,500/month Social Security.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Make aliyah through Jewish Agency. Join Maccabi HMO. Add Maccabi Sheli supplementary. Cigna for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Health tax (included in taxes) + supplementary ~₪250/month + Cigna ~₪1,200/month (Israel excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Jewish Couple, Both 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Making aliyah together. Combined UK pension £2,800/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Aliyah through Jewish Agency. Join Clalit. Add supplementary. BUPA for UK visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> HMO via health tax + supplementary ~₪400/month combined + BUPA ~₪2,800/month (Israel excluded).</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Non-Jewish American Spouse, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Non-Jewish spouse of Israeli citizen. Moving to Tel Aviv.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> A/5 temporary residence through spouse. Cigna Global while awaiting full status. Eventually eligible for HMO.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Initially Cigna ~₪1,600/month. After status: HMO + Cigna (Israel excluded) ~₪1,200/month.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can non-Jews retire to Israel?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Difficult without Israeli connections. Israel doesn't have a retirement visa. Options include: marriage to Israeli citizen (A/5 visa), employment, or certain investment pathways. Extended tourist stays are possible but not permanent residence. The Law of Return is primary immigration pathway.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does aliyah healthcare work?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Upon making aliyah, you immediately become an Israeli citizen with all rights. You must choose one of four HMOs (kupot holim). Coverage is funded through health tax automatically deducted from income. Coverage is comprehensive—hospitalization, specialists, prescriptions. Supplementary insurance adds faster access and extras.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Israeli healthcare really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent—among the world's best. High life expectancy, low infant mortality, advanced medical research. Hospitals like Hadassah and Sheba are globally recognized. Israel has more physicians per capita than most countries. The HMO system is efficient despite heavy use.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about security concerns?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Israel has security challenges—this is reality. Most areas where retirees live (Tel Aviv, Netanya, Herzliya) are generally safe. Security services are sophisticated. Israelis live normal lives despite regional tensions. Assess your comfort level; many retirees feel safe and enjoy life there.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that work well for Israel retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Israeli authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
